2. INSTALLING AND RUNNING FIELDS OF BATTLE 
------------------------------------------


2.1. INSTALLING
---------------

AMIGA

  1. Change to the directory where you want the Fields of Battle directory
     created. Unpack all supplied archives (with directory structure. This is
     the default on normal packers with inteligent authors, but if you use 
     PKUNZIP, remember the -d switch).

  2. Just run the program from Workbench.
     

  Use the ScreenMd (included with FOB) to select screen mode. Note FoB
  have direct support for CyberGraphics.



2.2. RUNNING
------------

  Amiga-Users: Double click on the Fob_131b directory icon to bring up the
               Fields of Battle window. Double click on the DemoFOB program
               icon to start the program. (If you want to use a screenmode
               that differs from your Workbench, doubleclick the ScreenMd
               icon, and select the mode you want). 
           


3. REGISTERING THE FULL GAME
----------------------------

3.1. WHAT YOU WILL GET
----------------------

When you have sent your registration and payment, you will recieve the full
version of Fields of Battle. This includes:

1. The full game
The full game will contain all features not available in the Free demo 
version. You can read about them in the on-line help and encyclopedia 
included in this demo version.

2. All 9 missions
All 9 missions will be available to you, especially the 9th mission will give
you the ultimative challenge in playing Fields of Battle.

3. Manual
The manual will help you getting started, selecting the right basic strategies
and is a good supplement to the on-line help system.

4. On-line help system
The on-line help system is an easy and quick way to help you with your
questions when playing Fields of Battle.

5. Encyclopedia
Close connected to the on-line help is the Encyclopedia over Fields of Battle
and World War I. Here you can read about World War I, giving you the
background for the scenarios and how you can use military units in Fields of
Battle.

6. Tables
The tables are very important when playing Fields of Battle. They describe the
hit probability for the military units in the different geographical types of
areas. The tables are also available in the on-line help, but they are much
faster available on paper, so all tables will be included on paper for easy
reference.

7. Map
Also the play map will be included on paper for easy overview and strategic
planning.

8. Installation tool for easy instaling Fields of Battle. For PC users an 
uninstall tool will be included.

9. For AMIGA users: Versions optimized for different processors.


